HAPPY WOMEN’S DAY 🫶💗 … it’s our day today & here’s a reminder that we’re so strong, beautiful, and powerful ❤️ & everything you set out to be you can achieve. It all starts with US. In having the confidence that it WILL work out! Not a maybe, not a hope so, and not a someday. But you knowing that it will happen and it’s just timing or redirection.  No matter how bad things are going or get, the present doesn’t dictate your future! Have trust in yourself and whatever you believe in (universe, God, etc) that things will work out and you will live out your dream life ✨

You actually do deserve everything great this world has to offer you ❤️‍🔥

Like Cancun/Cabo🇲🇽, but ready to experience real Mexican culture?  Oaxaca in July is such a fun time  for culture celebration festival in MX!!! 🍻 Mezcal shots, some of the beat Mexican food, live music, folkloric festivals in the street etc!!! 

Last 2 weekends of July is “La Guelaguetza” a festival celebrating cultures with food, music, dances, and Mezcal!! 

You get to visit “La feria del Mezcal” where you pay a $5-$10 fee and do Mezcal tastings from over 50 Mezcal brand producers. 

Saturday there’s the festival in the lively streets of oaxaca where each region has its live music, dancing, and passing around shots to the public!! 

Sunday “lunes del cerro” is where you can see all the dance performances on an auditorium on top of a mountain. 

And of course you can enjoy beautiful beaches like Huatulco and Puerto Escondido 🌊☀️🏝️

Had the privilege of having  @_empoderandomujeres as our tour guide ❗️‼️

I love Cancun too, but if you’re trying to be an actual traveler, Oaxaca is such a fun and enriching time!!

I’m actually so terrified! But sharing big news 🎉

I hate routine & this is something that has ALWAYS been in the back of my head but probably attachment has been the main thing stopping me.

All the things going on in my life have pushed me to finally just do it without overthinking. Just me, my dog Toffee 🐾and Jesus 🤍

UPDATE: This past month I was in Thailand for 2 weeks, decided I was selling all my belongings to live in different parts of the world (had 1 week to pack my whole life), then flew to Tulum & was there for 5 days, and now I came over to visit my Grandma in Oaxaca Mexico lol. 

For those wondering about Toffee (my puppy) 🐶 my parents are bringing him over on Monday. 
Tulúm was a preplanned trip from months ago, so I wasn’t going to take him to that lol. 

I’ll maybe spend the holidays with all my family here in Oaxaca and from there we’ll see where we choose to live first 🥰💓🌎

Ps: I need to post the Thailand & Tulum content bc it’s soooo much fun & want to share for when yall visit!!!
